<p>The DEQM Organization Profile defines the constraints for representing the organization for which the practitioner was working when he performed the measure to which he is attesting.</p>

<h3 id="mandatory-data-elements-and-terminology">Mandatory Data Elements and Terminology</h3>

<p>The following data-elements are mandatory (i.e data MUST be present).</p>

<p><strong>Each Organization must have:</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>Either an NPI or EIN (TIN) identifier</li>
</ol>

<!--

Each Organization *should* have ([Must Support](guidance.html#must-support)):

1. The beneficiary

-->

<p><strong>Additional Profile specific implementation guidance:</strong></p>

<p>The “Full View” tab below displays all the identifier slices including the <em>TIN</em> slice defined in this guide and <em>NPI</em> slice which is inherited indirectly from the <a href="http://hl7.org/fhir/us/core/STU3.1/StructureDefinition-us-core-organization.html">US Core Organization Profile</a>.</p>

